cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.IT, cs.MA 

This paper discusses communication protocols for Intermittently Connected Delay-Tolerant Wireless Sensor Networks (ICDT-WSNs), which are a subset of Wireless Sensor Networks (WSNs). Therefore, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the intermittent connectivity of Delay-Tolerant Networks (DTNs), which falls under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also examines communication protocols from the perspective of ICDT-WSNs, which involves information theory and mathematical analysis, falling under cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems).
